<refnamediv>
<refname>Tk_ClearSelection</refname>
<refpurpose>Deselect a selection</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>
<!-- body begins here -->
<refsynopsisdiv xml:id='synopsis'>
<funcsynopsis>
<funcsynopsisinfo>
#include &lt;tk.h&gt;

</funcsynopsisinfo>
<funcprototype>
<funcdef><function>Tk_ClearSelection</function></funcdef>
<paramdef><parameter>tkwin</parameter></paramdef>
<paramdef><parameter>selection</parameter></paramdef>
</funcprototype>
</funcsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>


<refsect1 xml:id='arguments'><title>ARGUMENTS</title>
<!-- .AS Tk_Window tkwin -->
<informaltable>
<tgroup cols='3'>
<tbody>

<row><entry>"Tk_Window"</entry><entry>"tkwin"</entry><entry>"in"</entry>
<entry>
<para>The selection will be cleared from the display containing this
window.</para>
</entry>
</row>
<row><entry>Atom</entry><entry>selection</entry><entry>in</entry>
<entry>
<para>The name of selection to be cleared.</para>
<!-- .BE -->
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</informaltable>

</refsect1>

<refsect1 xml:id='description'><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
<para><function>Tk_ClearSelection</function> cancels the selection specified by the atom 
<emphasis remap='I'>selection</emphasis> for the display containing <emphasis remap='I'>tkwin</emphasis>.
The selection need not be in <emphasis remap='I'>tkwin</emphasis> itself or even in
<emphasis remap='I'>tkwin</emphasis>'s application.
If there is a window anywhere on <emphasis remap='I'>tkwin</emphasis>'s display that
owns <emphasis remap='I'>selection</emphasis>, the window will be notified and the
selection will be cleared.
If there is no owner for <emphasis remap='I'>selection</emphasis> on the display, then the
procedure has no effect.</para>

</refsect1>

<refsect1 xml:id='keywords'><title>KEYWORDS</title>
<para>clear, selection</para>
</refsect1>
